[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Figuring out the workflow setup**\n\nTo fix the workflow, I should start with the current version setup and consider existing tests. The driver might need to update the version, but if the current build.gradle already has the necessary properties, we might not need anything extra. Before generation, it’s important to prepare deterministic setup entries. If there’s a failure with the native image run on an existing library version, the driver likely clones the current test folder. Let’s decide on the setup needed to achieve meaningful test coverage.\n\n**Investigating dependencies and documentation**\n\nThe build already contains extra dependencies, so I can return advisory preparation with slf4j-api. I need to be precise and investigate the resolved artifacts and how they are typically used, including checking the documentation. Collecting evidence from the docs is essential. According to the JGroups manual, JChannel and UDP defaults use bind_addr and IP multicast, which I can summarize. It’s also important to mention any risks related to native verification. Let’s quickly fetch the relevant documentation.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f9d41f312c45f7c016a42690a5c308193abc99624f5581799\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQmkViOnwvxcGN5pwBowrl0NNO7ffNjL2FIyZ5944CpPSE-S3bJ4xw3cmY7oJ3xLvTBWI0Kxf8Ww05bDyCUbKPgjROmtStPTrImJuuM78buLKtnS8oAXd4LFbFGieH1mC0qEE1kugwYo4eXWecw6d1p-FXWWnBMVZS206jhUvpUEpSe7QNy0T26UhX4SGhzJU3pXu_1clhQd1faSvifK-a31F3BmXWKcngn3-HfbpbOqSf5nE8K4YKDrv16nArlE1eEmgK6nAx83xZNZxtO-0ZDhmQyR5ezqVUVgKJuUN2xNfMxTe2fHmt0SfjHx4xDnEzRR5DrH-Sc_PbUuJy_vmSOA5RXFSptou_rMfSpNxoTCrzNJJKXR05avlkAG_XZlImhcwJFdRE_khi8fpaz1HgumBVEquSa5phh6enRqZRIUtHs4cKdANODhVlbBZYi4w6kV2QX5mYFSv_NPyxSfK-LLRLNBB3K2YYvvYn4gDe5n89AnhdTTkfczsk4woL_eXeB34csXqOASdFHLC0xssZbHBI5mPU2CFdHphZud-alaSeuYckU_xw0yq7NvCFCrWzi2ggrCXeJ-V7wE4m6bmyRV-hg-XYoH